article.headline: Wofford 74, Elon 71
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- Junior Salters scored 20 points, including nine of Wofford's 10 points in overtime, to propel the Terriers to a 74-71 win against Elon on Monday night. Elon led by three points at halftime, and for the entire second half until Salters hit a jumper to tie the score at 60-all with 2:34 left in regulation. After another tie at 62-62, Ola Atoyebi's layup put Elon ahead by two with 37 seconds left. But Tim Johnson hit a pair of free throws with 20 seconds on the clock that would hold up, sending the game into overtime. Salters took over from there. Noah Dahlman scored 18, and Johnson finished with 14 points and 10 rebounds for the Terriers (8-9, 4-4 Southern Conference). Atoyebi led the Phoenix (5-12, 2-7) with 17, Monty Sanders scored 15 and Brett James added 11.
